node.text:
The Curse of Anubis ⁠
⁠
Credit: Trevor Gallois⁠
⁠
"This is the final year project that was put together in a year by myself and Laure Cornu.  We had to create a short trailer with a theme of our choice. We decided to go with a very classic one and try to create a trailer for a game. I was in charge of everything but the character modeling and rigging/animation and monster rig (Done by Laure Cornu). The sound was also made by myself.⁠
In the end, we had to present our project in front of a group of professionals. It was a...difficult project, to say the least. I'm happy that we could hand out something in hand, albeit it had lots of problems. Many learning/changing camera shots/storyboard rework in a hurry, some last-minute changes, as a lot of part of the project was a first, such as the character rigging or animation, and the implementation in Unreal Engine. I used FluidNinja for the VFX, which is a very cool plugin for Unreal. I want to focus more on the environment and lighting now, as I've always enjoyed this part.⁠
I'm glad I'm done with this project, haha."⁠
⁠
